David W. Johnson
June 27, 1963 - July 9, 2017


David W. Johnson, 54, of Waseca, died Sunday morning July 9, 2017 of injuries sustained in an automobile accident. David was born June 27, 1963, in Charles City, IA, to Doyle and Lola (Lou) Johnson. David loved hunting, snowmobiling and his passion was riding his Harley Davidson. He loved spending time with his 3 grandchildren. David is survived by his wife Lori of Waseca, daughter Natasha (Nick) Kahnke of Waseca, sons Casey (Alex White) of Owatonna, and Cody (Brianna Marble) of Owatonna. Three grandchildren Aliyah, Haley, and Ashton Kahnke. Three brothers Dean (Terri) Johnson from Florida; Scott (Sandy) Johnson from Nora Springs, IA; Todd (Robin) Johnson of Tennesee, and sister Patty (Dan) Bilharz of Nashua, IA. He is preceded in death by his parents, Doyle Johnson and Lola (Lou) Reetz, sister April Martin and nephew Dillon Johnson. A memorial gathering will be held Saturday, July 15, 2017 at 2 p.m. at Blowers Park in Waseca, with a small prayer service at 3 p.m.

